## Post 34: Fixture Boundary

Short post:

> The OSS showcase demo is intentionally fixture-first. Do not post it as a pandas fix or a live GitHub scout result. The honest claim is the packet boundary: complete evidence can pass; incomplete evidence blocks.

Evidence:

- `docs/outreach/FIFTH-WAVE-OSS-PROOF-SHOWCASE-2026-07-02.md`
- `docs/outreach/receipts/fifth-wave/oss-showcase-fixture-ready-evidence.json`
- `docs/outreach/receipts/fifth-wave/oss-showcase-fixture-blocked-evidence.json`

## Operating Rule

Pair the ready fixture with the blocked fixture. The product claim is not "we can auto-open PRs"; the claim is that public work can be packaged into evidence-gated handoffs before a human decides whether to publish.
